sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K777122
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: yhjH under the control of constitutive promoter J23100
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Team Goettingen
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The product of this gene is a phosphodiesterase which is involved in regulating the levels of c-di-GMP, a bacterial signaling molecule. High levels of c-di-GMP promote biofilm synthesis and inhibit flagella by binding to YcgR which then acts as a "brake" on FliG and FliM. Levels of c-di-GMP are elevated and motility is reduced in ''yhjH''-mutants.
Here we used 3 different constitutive [http://partsregistry.org/Part:BBa_J23100 Anderson promoters] from the 2006 Berkeley group to test how different levels of constitutive ''yhjH'' expression affect the motility of ''E. coli''.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: * ''yhjH'' was amplified from genomic DNA of ''E. coli'' DH10B via PCR using the following primers: ** Fwd: 5'-gtttcttcgaattcgcggccgcttctagatgataaggcaggttatccagc-3' ** Rev: 5'-gtttcttcctgcagcggccgctactagtattatagcgccagaaccgccgtattcagc-3'
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: * ''yhjH'' was amplified from genomic DNA of ''E. coli'' str. K-12 substr. DH10B, complete genome (CP000948.1). * J23100 information was taken from the partsregistry and physical DNA from the 2012 distribution kit.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2122000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Device expressing the Gb3 Synthase enzyme under control of an arabinose inducible promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sannia Farrukh
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part will code for Gb3 synthase. Gb3 synthase in return makes Gb3 which is a receptor for Shiga-like toxin (stx 1&2). Shiga-like toxins are exotoxins, which consist of a toxic enzymatic A subunit and a cell-binding B subunit. The latter binds to a globotriaosylceramide (Gb3) receptor, expressed on the surface of the target cells in humans. This interaction is responsible for the toxin's entry into the host cell. When the receptor is exposed to the food sample, the SLT subunit B, if present, will bind to Gb3.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: An inducible promoter (BBa_10500), RBS (BBa_B0034) Scar was added to the sequence. Along with a terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Coding Sequence from GenBank

The ''fliC'' gene codes for flagellin. This protein is the subunit that forms the flagellar filament of ''E. coli''.
Here we used 3 different constitutive [http://partsregistry.org/Part:BBa_J23100 Anderson promoters] from the 2006 Berkeley group to test how different levels of constitutive ''fliC'' expression affect the motility or flagellum size of ''E. coli''.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: * The ''fliC'' gene contained three PstI sites and one SpeI site that had to be removed. These mutations were induced with different primers via overlap-PCR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: * The ''fliC'' gene was amplified from genomic DNA of ''E. coli'' str. K-12 substr. DH10B, complete genome (CP000948.1).
